subSubSection.paragraph:
Chthonius inguscioi
differs from
C. multidentatus
in the following main characters: anterior eyes with flat lens, posterior eyes reduced to a pale cuticular area (no eyes in
C. multidentatus
); anterior margin of carapace with 2 preocular microsetae on each side (1 preocular microseta in
C. multidentatus
); fixed and movable chelal fingers of male with 68–77 and 53–56 teeth, respectively (male with 83 and 60 in
C. multidentatus
).
